                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Casters have been the dev teams baby for over a year now?   <br /><br />I can hardly recall casters getting ANY balance like warriors did when they did melee balance 1.0.  IMO they still have not done caster balance 1.0 and are already going back to melee.  <br /><br />And adding items to balance casters is not caster balancing.  Chars should be balanced NAKED!  Melee balance was done mostly on an innate level.  Skills, HP adjust, etc.   Adding items for casters is not balance.  <br /><br />As far as the dot focus items that are in game.  NONE of the items that are in the game improve the DPS of DoTs.  They only make them more mana efficent.   That was not the answer.  Necros more than any caster class suffer from their spell effectiveness and ability to do DPS since Kunark and have yet to be adjusted to be where we should be.  Our Damage / mana ratio should be greatly improved past a wizards best DD pre focus/aa for either class.   Why?  Because it takes us anywhere form 42 sec to 2 min per spell to do full damage for 1 cast.  Necros should be the reigning class for DPS in fights over 6 min.  Unfortunately wizards keep DPS far above what we can accomplish on long fights and that is not how it should be.  If I can stack on 5 DoTs and they run full term, and with my mana regen am able to keep them stacked on a mob nonstop for the duration of a 20 min fight,  my DPS should be FAR better than a wizards.  Of course, this is being taken into account of how necro vs. wizard was when the game came out.  Wizards were given more and more power, necros just kind of stayed at the same lvl.   <br /><br />How about they do proper caster balancing before saying melee have fallen behind?  If you increase the efficiency of melee too much, what is the advantage of being a caster who is dependant upon mana anymore?<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
