                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Alot of really good things coming up.  The ability to save spell setups is a great feature and the DoT changes are a step in the right direction.  What I am most interested in is the upcoming revamps of some old world zones.  After spending hours upon hours raiding in PoP, the last freaking thing I want to do is XP there!  So I would love to be able to return to some of my favorite old world XP zones (like HS and DN) and see a positive XP progression.<br /><br />&lt;&lt;Doesn't that represent a reduction in the total hunting space for those levels? These people have fewer dungeon options available now&gt;&gt;<br /><br />Sorry but there are tons of content for players under 60th level which is never even used anymore by players.  If they are not going to use those zones, they may aswell convert them to help offset the crowding of the 60th+ level crowd.<br /><br />&lt;&lt;Since it represents the same amount of work to create a new zone as to replace an old one&gt;&gt;<br /><br />It takes far <b>LESS</b> work to revamp older zones then create new ones from the ground up.  All the texture modeling are already done, pathing is worked out and the basic layout of the zone is completed.  All they really have to do is re-evaluate the mobs and the item drops when revamping a zone.<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
